00:46:02,662 --> 00:46:04,431
This guy
    will take care of you.

1052
00:46:04,497 --> 00:46:08,868
Well, what if
      I change my mind?

1053
00:46:08,935 --> 00:46:10,603
I do
  I got my money.

1054
00:46:12,339 --> 00:46:13,940
(Arizona)
       Who's there?

1055
00:46:14,007 --> 00:46:15,775
It's Glen.

1056
00:46:15,842 --> 00:46:19,079
Glen, welcome.

1057
00:46:19,145 --> 00:46:21,014
I got somebody
here to see you.

1058
00:46:21,081 --> 00:46:22,649
Well, come on down
 and bring him over.

1059
00:46:22,716 --> 00:46:24,217
All right,
you go.

1060
00:46:24,284 --> 00:46:25,352
I'll wait here.

1061
00:46:25,418 --> 00:46:26,419
You're not
      gonna goith me?

1062
00:46:26,486 --> 00:46:28,822
It's cool.
  Don't worry about it.

1063
00:46:28,888 --> 00:46:30,857
(Jules)
 Hi.

1064
00:46:45,138 --> 00:46:46,740
So what can I do for you, son?

1065
00:46:46,806 --> 00:46:50,276
Well, Glen said that, um...

1066
00:46:50,343 --> 00:46:52,812
Glen said what?

1067
00:46:52,879 --> 00:46:54,981
Glen said that you break hands.

1068
00:46:55,048 --> 00:46:57,717
Yes.

1069
00:46:57,784 --> 00:46:59,052
That's absolutely right.

1070
00:47:01,187 --> 00:47:02,822
And whose hands
  are we talking about?

1071
00:47:04,891 --> 00:47:06,793
Mine.

1072
00:47:25,912 --> 00:47:26,980
Oh, sheez.

1073
00:47:27,047 --> 00:47:27,981
I'm s--oh, oh.

1074
00:47:28,048 --> 00:47:29,015
I'm sorry.

1075
00:47:29,082 --> 00:47:30,784
I'm so--
      my fault.

1076
00:47:30,850 --> 00:47:31,751
Everything okay?

1077
00:47:31,818 --> 00:47:33,353
I'm fine.

1078
00:47:33,420 --> 00:47:36,856
Just maybe a few too many
      Christmas parties, but...

1079
00:47:36,923 --> 00:47:38,091
You meant me,
  didn't you?

1080
00:47:38,158 --> 00:47:39,559
[laughing]
Right.

1081
00:47:39,626 --> 00:47:41,261
I was just checking.

1082
00:47:41,327 --> 00:47:43,963
Um...

1083
00:47:44,030 --> 00:47:45,432
So how's Helen?

1084
00:47:45,498 --> 00:47:49,636
Well, her blood pressure's
still a little high,

1085
00:47:49,703 --> 00:47:51,304
but it's much improved
since this morning.

1086
00:47:51,371 --> 00:47:52,872
Good.

1087
00:47:52,939 --> 00:47:56,009
But she's still
 not eating.

1088
00:47:56,076 --> 00:47:58,311
And I'm very concerned
    about that.

1089
00:47:58,378 --> 00:48:01,114
If she doesn't
eat something tonigh    I'm gonna come back  a little later and...

1090
00:48:01,181 --> 00:48:03,016
check on her.

1091
00:48:07,954 --> 00:48:08,888
All right.

1092
00:48:08,955 --> 00:48:10,290
Let's start
the celebration

1093
00:48:10,357 --> 00:48:13,426
with some carrot cake,
huh?

1094
00:48:13,493 --> 00:48:15,462
Let's see.

1095
00:48:15,528 --> 00:48:17,163
Here we go.

1096
00:48:20,533 --> 00:48:22,369
Just a little nibble.

1097
00:48:22,435 --> 00:48:23,703
Here you go, Mom.

1098
00:48:23,770 --> 00:48:25,839
Come on.

1099
00:48:25,905 --> 00:48:27,507
Please.

1100
00:48:27,574 --> 00:48:28,508
Come on.

1101
00:48:28,575 --> 00:48:29,542
Did you hear
the doctor?

1102
00:48:29,609 --> 00:48:31,277
It's really important
that you eat, okay?

1103
00:48:31,344 --> 00:48:33,346
Let's just try,
just a little nibble.

1104
00:48:33,413 --> 00:48:34,814
Please.

1105
00:48:34,881 --> 00:48:37,050
Come on.

1106
00:48:37,117 --> 00:48:39,085
Why won't you
eat anything?

1107
00:48:39,152 --> 00:48:41,421
[sighing]
Oh, God.

1108
00:48:44,424 --> 00:48:46,126
Okay, let's do the tree.

1109
00:48:46,192 --> 00:48:49,896
Look what I won, Mom.

1110
00:48:49,963 --> 00:48:51,431
Huh, nice tree?

1111
00:48:51,498 --> 00:48:54,267
It'll cheer up
the room.

1112
00:48:54,334 --> 00:48:55,268
Okay.

1113
00:48:55,335 --> 00:48:56,836
Let's see.

1114
00:49:02,542 --> 00:49:04,411
You like that, Mom,
    hm?

1115
00:49:04,477 --> 00:49:05,745
Merry Christmas.

1116
00:49:05,812 --> 00:49:07,080
[hissing]

1117
00:49:07,147 --> 00:49:08,381
Oh.

1118
00:49:08,448 --> 00:49:09,449
[laughing]
      Hold on.
  I'll get it.

1119
00:49:09,516 --> 00:49:10,583
I can fix it.

1120
00:49:10,650 --> 00:49:12,352
Let's see.

1121
00:49:12,419 --> 00:49:14,754
Just a little bit of...

1122
00:49:14,821 --> 00:49:17,657
What the hell's
 wrong with this thing?

1123
00:49:17,724 --> 00:49:19,225
Ah, just get this.

1124
00:49:19,292 --> 00:49:20,193
I'm gonna fix it.

1125
00:49:20,260 --> 00:49:22,796
Don't worry.

1126
00:49:22,862 --> 00:49:24,564
Damn it!

1127
00:49:26,966 --> 00:49:28,868
[sighs]

1128
00:49:28,935 --> 00:49:31,838
[somber music]

1129
00:49:31,905 --> 00:49:39,813
^^ ^^

1130
00:50:15,815 --> 00:50:18,018
I love you.

1131
00:50:20,186 --> 00:50:28,094
^^ ^^

1132
00:50:33,633 --> 00:50:34,734
(woman)
   Get him in room two.

1133
00:50:36,870 --> 00:50:38,138
What's going on here?

1134
00:50:38,204 --> 00:50:39,806
It's a pileup
on the West Side Highway.

1135
00:50:39,873 --> 00:50:41,174
[woman screaming]
     You save him!

1136
00:50:41,241 --> 00:50:42,709
He needs help!

1137
00:50:42,776 --> 00:50:44,511
(man)
 Sir, I'll be
 right with you.

1138
00:50:44,577 --> 00:50:45,745
Looking for my mother.

1139
00:50:45,812 --> 00:50:47,414
She was involved
    in an accident on the highway.

1140
00:50:47,480 --> 00:50:48,815
Her name
 is Evelyn Jents.

1141
00:50:48,882 --> 00:50:51,484
I guess there isn't
  gonna be a party now.

1142
00:50:51,551 --> 00:50:53,420
Not tonight, sweetie.

1143
00:50:53,486 --> 00:50:56,556
I'll try to scrounge up
some leftover eggnog for you.

1144
00:50:56,623 --> 00:50:58,024
Hi.

1145
00:50:58,091 --> 00:51:00,460
Sure wasn't like this
when I was 14.

1146
00:51:00,527 --> 00:51:02,662
That was the best Christmas
I ever had.

1147
00:51:02,729 --> 00:51:03,663
That's great.

1148
00:51:03,730 --> 00:51:04,798
Excuse me.

1149
00:51:04,864 --> 00:51:06,499
Excuse me,
but I've been waiting for hours.

1150
00:51:06,566 --> 00:51:08,034
Is there any news
on Artie Venezelos yet?

1151
00:51:08,101 --> 00:51:09,969
You're gonna have
  to talk to Nurse Stein.

1152
00:51:11,738 --> 00:51:12,672
Excuse me.

1153
00:51:12,739 --> 00:51:14,474
I was hoping
you could give me some news

1154
00:51:14,541 --> 00:51:15,442
on Artie Venezelos.

1155
00:51:15,508 --> 00:51:16,676
Are you family?

1156
00:51:16,743 --> 00:51:18,378
No, not really.
I just--

1157
00:51:18,445 --> 00:51:20,113
Either you are,
  or you're not.

1158
00:51:21,781 --> 00:51:22,949
I'm a friend.

1159
00:51:23,016 --> 00:51:24,351
I'm sorry;
I can't give out

1160
00:51:24,417 --> 00:51:25,552
any medical information.

1161
00:51:25,618 --> 00:51:26,653
He's his friend.

1162
00:51:26,720 --> 00:51:28,555
You know,
like his friend-friend.

1163
00:51:28,621 --> 00:51:29,989
I don't care
  if he's his priest.

1164
00:51:30,056 --> 00:51:31,691
Okay, thank you,
Nurse Ratched.

1165
00:51:31,758 --> 00:51:33,493
Listen.

1166
00:51:33,560 --> 00:51:35,028
I will find out
      what I can, okay?

1167
00:51:35,095 --> 00:51:36,463
Oh, man,
I really appreciate that.

1168
00:51:36,529 --> 00:51:37,664
You know,
but the truth of it is,

1169
00:51:37,731 --> 00:51:38,898
we're not even
really friends.

1170
00:51:38,965 --> 00:51:40,233
Really?

1171
00:51:41,401 --> 00:51:42,569
It's okay.

1172
00:51:42,635 --> 00:51:44,738
I figured that.

1173
00:51:52,545 --> 00:52:00,420
[somber music]
    ^^ ^^

1174
00:52:21,975 --> 00:52:22,909
(man)
 Can't swim.

1175
00:52:22,976 --> 00:52:24,411
[gasping]

1176
00:52:24,477 --> 00:52:27,814
Love to learn.

1177
00:52:27,881 --> 00:52:29,182
You're the guy
    from the hospital.

1178
00:52:29,249 --> 00:52:30,183
Yeah, Charlie Boyd.

1179
00:52:30,250 --> 00:52:31,217
You're the angel lady.

1180
00:52:32,919 --> 00:52:34,421
What are you doing here?

1181
00:52:34,487 --> 00:52:35,722
Did you follow me?

1182
00:52:35,789 --> 00:52:37,924
No, not at all.

1183
00:52:37,991 --> 00:52:39,659
Well, then,
well, why are you here?

1184
00:52:39,726 --> 00:52:41,628
I could ask you
    the same question.

1185
00:52:41,695 --> 00:52:43,730
I just want you
    to leave me alone.

1186
00:52:43,797 --> 00:52:44,731
Can't do that.

1187
00:52:44,798 --> 00:52:45,899
I see a woman
standing alone

1188
00:52:45,965 --> 00:52:47,701
on a pier looking over a ledge,
  I gotta help.

1189
00:52:47,767 --> 00:52:50,003
I don't want any help.

1190
00:52:50,070 --> 00:52:51,504
If you jump in,
I'm gonna have to

1191
00:52:51,571 --> 00:52:52,839
jump in right after you.

1192
00:52:52,906 --> 00:52:55,308
Who said anything
      about jumping in?

1193
00:52:55,375 --> 00:52:57,644
But if I did jump,
   you'd jump in after me

1194
00:52:57,711 --> 00:53:00,080
after you told me
  that you can't swim?

1195
00:53:00,146 --> 00:53:02,816
Yeah, because it's
the right thing to do.

1196
00:53:02,882 --> 00:53:04,117
And you always do
      the right thing?

1197
00:53:04,184 --> 00:53:05,418
Yeah, I do.

1198
00:53:05,485 --> 00:53:06,953
It's a bad habit.

1199
00:53:09,823 --> 00:53:11,524
You want to tell me
 your sad story?

1200
00:53:11,591 --> 00:53:15,395
I'm a really good
      listener.

1201
00:53:15,462 --> 00:53:18,398
I'm all ears.

1202
00:53:18,465 --> 00:53:20,633
Good,
  I'll tell you mine.

1203
00:53:20,700 --> 00:53:24,971
It's Christmas Eve,
    and I'm all alone.

1204
00:53:27,707 --> 00:53:28,775
That's it?

1205
00:53:28,842 --> 00:53:30,510
You're all alone?

1206
00:53:30,577 --> 00:53:32,112
That's the best
    you can do?

1207
00:53:32,178 --> 00:53:34,080
There's more.

1208
00:53:34,147 --> 00:53:35,382
I'm a priest.

1209
00:53:35,448 --> 00:53:36,683
Really?

1210
00:53:36,750 --> 00:53:37,984
Yeah, for 20 years.

1211
00:53:38,051 --> 00:53:40,286
Then last year,
I left the priesthood.

1212
00:53:40,353 --> 00:53:42,655
Kicked the habit.

1213
00:53:42,722 --> 00:53:44,491
Started my life over.

1214
00:53:44,557 --> 00:53:46,393
Now here I am.

1215
00:53:46,459 --> 00:53:47,861
No more
Catholic family,

1216
00:53:47,927 --> 00:53:49,396
no personal family here,

1217
00:53:49,462 --> 00:53:51,865
no one.

1218
00:53:51,931 --> 00:53:53,767
Wow.

1219
00:53:53,833 --> 00:53:55,368
Now you want me
  to guess yours?

1220
00:53:55,435 --> 00:53:58,238
Take your best shot.

1221
00:53:58,304 --> 00:54:00,206
You're an attractive lady
  who forgot her hat,

1222
00:54:00,273 --> 00:54:01,875
and your ears
    are very cold.

1223
00:54:01,941 --> 00:54:03,076
Bingo.

1224
00:54:03,143 --> 00:54:04,344
Hah.

1225
00:54:04,411 --> 00:54:05,912
Take anything
    off the top shelf.

1226
00:54:09,015 --> 00:54:11,317
Want to get a cab
      and get a cup of coffee,

1227
00:54:11,384 --> 00:54:13,887
and I'll guess more
of your story?

1228
00:54:21,261 --> 00:54:23,329
After you.

1229
00:54:24,698 --> 00:54:27,567
[melodramatic music]

1230
00:54:27,634 --> 00:54:32,539
^^ ^^

1231
00:54:32,605 --> 00:54:34,941
Still my turn
       to guess, Rose?

1232
00:54:35,008 --> 00:54:36,910
You're this amazing person,

1233
00:54:36,976 --> 00:54:38,878
but you're too busy
    helping others

1234
00:54:38,945 --> 00:54:42,449
to see it.

1235
00:54:42,515 --> 00:54:45,185
You take good care
of your friend, right?

1236
00:54:45,251 --> 00:54:46,820
Thanks.

1237
00:54:46,886 --> 00:54:48,822
Is he a close friend?

1238
00:54:50,990 --> 00:54:53,593
What's the matter?

1239
00:54:53,660 --> 00:54:56,296
Kind of a bad stomach.

1240
00:54:56,363 --> 00:54:59,065
[gasping]
    Hurts.

1241
00:54:59,132 --> 00:55:01,267
Hope we get
  someplace soon.

1242
00:55:06,973 --> 00:55:08,608
I don't feel
so good.

1243
00:55:08,675 --> 00:55:10,710
All right, well...

1244
00:55:10,777 --> 00:55:13,480
My place is actually
not far from here.

1245
00:55:13,546 --> 00:55:15,281
Do you want
to go there?

1246
00:55:15,348 --> 00:55:16,783
You sure?
    Yeah.

1247
00:55:16,850 --> 00:55:19,519
Driver,
three lights,

1248
00:55:19,586 --> 00:55:21,421
take a left.

1249
00:55:22,589 --> 00:55:24,491
Hey, you know, I really
appreciate you doing this.

1250
00:55:24,557 --> 00:55:25,825
Aw, man,
I'm glad I could help.

1251
00:55:25,892 --> 00:55:27,727
I know hospital policy
      isn't always on our side.

1252
00:55:27,794 --> 00:55:28,895
They can be
      a little stuffy.

1253
00:55:28,962 --> 00:55:30,263
I remember when
  my lover got sick--

1254
00:55:30,330 --> 00:55:31,531
Hey, wait, wait.
Wait a minute.

1255
00:55:31,598 --> 00:55:33,066
You made a mistake,
uh, Randy.

1256
00:55:33,133 --> 00:55:34,801
Yeah, you're making
the wrong assumption

1257
00:55:34,868 --> 00:55:35,869
about Artie and I.

1258
00:55:35,935 --> 00:55:38,138
I appreciate you
bringing me up here and all,

1259
00:55:38,204 --> 00:55:39,706
but the truth of it is,
we ain't a couple.

1260
00:55:39,773 --> 00:55:41,141
As a matter of fact,
I just met the guy.

1261
00:55:41,207 --> 00:55:42,809
He's a waiter,
and I ordered some coffee--

1262
00:55:42,876 --> 00:55:44,577
Oh, my God,
    that's how my parents met.

1263
00:55:44,644 --> 00:55:46,046
My mother
waited on my father,

1264
00:55:46,112 --> 00:55:47,447
only he ordered
a tuna fish sandwich

1265
00:55:47,514 --> 00:55:48,481
and a ginger ale.

1266
00:55:48,581 --> 00:55:49,883
No, now, now look.

1267
00:55:49,949 --> 00:55:52,052
I just, I want
to make it clear that--

1268
00:55:52,118 --> 00:55:53,586
Don't worry.

1269
00:55:53,653 --> 00:55:55,355
Your secret's
      safe with me.

1270
00:56:00,894 --> 00:56:02,228
He's stable now.

1271
00:56:02,295 --> 00:56:05,131
Just thank God
 for small blessings, right?

1272
00:56:05,198 --> 00:56:06,232
Let him know
you're here.

1273
00:56:06,299 --> 00:56:08,101
I don't care
      what the doctors say.

1274
00:56:08,168 --> 00:56:09,803
Talk to him.
 Tell him how you feel.

1275
00:56:09,869 --> 00:56:11,204
He'll hear you.

1276
00:56:11,271 --> 00:56:13,273
Mike,
    we got to talk.

1277
00:56:13,340 --> 00:56:14,341
Oh, hi.

1278
00:56:14,407 --> 00:56:15,342
Oh, my.

1279
00:56:15,408 --> 00:56:16,309
Who's that?

1280
00:56:16,376 --> 00:56:17,610
Nah, forget about it.

1281
00:56:17,677 --> 00:56:19,279
What do you got?
    I went
  to the station.

1282
00:56:19,346 --> 00:56:20,680
I got some info
on this guy.

1283
00:56:20,747 --> 00:56:22,816
Did you know your friend here
      served four years

1284
00:56:22,882 --> 00:56:26,186
on a ten-year sentence
  for manslaughter back in '79?

1285
00:56:26,252 --> 00:56:28,355
This guy?
      Yeah, that's him.

1286
00:56:28,421 --> 00:56:30,090
It was
  a domestic dispute.

1287
00:56:30,156 --> 00:56:32,459
This Venezelos
  comes home,

1288
00:56:32,525 --> 00:56:34,160
finds his wife
with another guy, right,

1289
00:56:34,227 --> 00:56:36,096
but it's no boyfriend
  or nothing,

1290
00:56:36,162 --> 00:56:37,530
just an old friend.

1291
00:56:37,597 --> 00:56:39,032
He goes into a rage,

1292
00:56:39,099 --> 00:56:40,633
accuses her
  of being unfaithful, right?

1293
00:56:40,700 --> 00:56:42,602
Him and this guy
get into some words.

1294
00:56:42,669 --> 00:56:44,270
They start
going at each other.

1295
00:56:44,337 --> 00:56:46,873
He throws the guy
down a flight of stairs.

1296
00:56:46,940 --> 00:56:48,375
The guy's neck breaks.

1297
00:56:48,441 --> 00:56:49,743
He died
  in the hospital

1298
00:56:49,809 --> 00:56:50,744
a few hours later.

1299
00:56:50,810 --> 00:56:52,045
Wait,
    it gets worse.

1300
00:56:52,112 --> 00:56:54,614
The wife takes off
before the cops show up, right?

1301
00:56:54,681 --> 00:56:56,416
She jumps in her car
      and speeds away.

1302
00:56:56,483 --> 00:56:57,817
She's doing, like,
      about 80

1303
00:56:57,884 --> 00:56:59,819
when she skids out
      on this icy curve

1304
00:56:59,886 --> 00:57:02,355
and hits an oncoming car
      head on.

1305
00:57:02,422 --> 00:57:04,591
She was killed instantly.

1306
00:57:06,960 --> 00:57:08,495
Mike.

1307
00:57:10,497 --> 00:57:12,499
Whoa, Mikey,
   you all right?

1308
00:57:12,565 --> 00:57:13,733
Yeah.

1309
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:15,769
Yeah, I'm okay.

1310
00:57:15,835 --> 00:57:17,570
Well, at least we know
    who the nut is now, right?

1311
00:57:17,637 --> 00:57:19,339
Naw, he's not nuts.

1312
00:57:19,406 --> 00:57:20,607
Yeah, all right.
      Whatever.

1313
00:57:20,674 --> 00:57:22,008
Let's get out of here.
    I'll take you home.

