01:05:55,321 --> 01:05:57,691
My father
never talked about that.

1501
01:06:00,326 --> 01:06:02,529
Anyhow, I'm sorry.

1502
01:06:02,595 --> 01:06:05,365
Pop, you know,
he just can't seem to forget it.

1503
01:06:05,432 --> 01:06:07,934
It's the past
that holds onto him.

1504
01:06:08,001 --> 01:06:10,136
We don't count.

1505
01:06:10,203 --> 01:06:11,438
No matter what we do,

1506
01:06:11,504 --> 01:06:13,039
no matter how much
  we try to be there for him,

1507
01:06:13,106 --> 01:06:16,142
we just can't reach him.

1508
01:06:16,209 --> 01:06:18,745
I can't reach him.

1509
01:06:20,013 --> 01:06:21,014
Do you know he still keeps

1510
01:06:21,081 --> 01:06:22,816
that glass angel by his bed?

1511
01:06:24,150 --> 01:06:25,885
I swear he sees
her face in it.

1512
01:06:25,952 --> 01:06:29,022
Glass angel?

1513
01:06:29,089 --> 01:06:30,557
Yeah, my mother
      had it blown out of glass

1514
01:06:30,623 --> 01:06:32,058
to put on top of the tree.

1515
01:06:32,125 --> 01:06:34,861
It was a surprise for Pop.

1516
01:06:36,496 --> 01:06:38,865
Sounds like
they loved each other very much.

1517
01:06:38,932 --> 01:06:40,300
They did.

1518
01:06:41,835 --> 01:06:44,337
All my father's looking for
      is a little forgiveness.

1519
01:06:44,404 --> 01:06:45,772
Where's the harm in that?

1520
01:06:47,674 --> 01:06:49,976
Forgiveness from who?

1521
01:06:50,043 --> 01:06:51,911
From her.

1522
01:06:51,978 --> 01:06:54,848
He screwed up,
 and he's sorry.

1523
01:06:54,914 --> 01:06:57,851
He just never got a chance
  to tell her.

1524
01:07:03,923 --> 01:07:05,658
I got to take
a walk.

1525
01:07:05,725 --> 01:07:09,629
I'll be right back.

1526
01:07:09,696 --> 01:07:10,797
Keep an eye on him.

1527
01:07:10,864 --> 01:07:13,900
Yeah, you got it.

