I know.

1567
01:10:13,580 --> 01:10:15,515
That's why your mother
 wants you to let go

1568
01:10:15,582 --> 01:10:18,118
and live a life.

1569
01:10:18,184 --> 01:10:19,686
What?

1570
01:10:19,753 --> 01:10:21,988
Your mother wants you
      to live your life, Rose.

1571
01:10:22,055 --> 01:10:23,156
You don't know my mother.

1572
01:10:23,223 --> 01:10:24,057
She knows
       you love her

1573
01:10:24,124 --> 01:10:25,358
and you're there for her.

1574
01:10:25,425 --> 01:10:26,659
Why are you doing this?

1575
01:10:26,726 --> 01:10:27,994
Because she told me
  to tell you.

1576
01:10:28,061 --> 01:10:29,896
That's not funny.

1577
01:10:29,963 --> 01:10:31,498
And you're scaring me.

1578
01:10:31,564 --> 01:10:32,699
No, Rose,
  listen.

1579
01:10:32,766 --> 01:10:33,833
I don't have
    much time.

1580
01:10:33,900 --> 01:10:34,834
Charlie, please.

1581
01:10:34,901 --> 01:10:36,102
I don't want
to listen.

1582
01:10:36,169 --> 01:10:37,637
Please listen
    to what I have to say.

1583
01:10:37,704 --> 01:10:38,638
Get out of the house.

1584
01:10:38,705 --> 01:10:39,806
I don't want you
here anymore.

1585
01:10:39,873 --> 01:10:40,974
I'm not gonna leave

1586
01:10:41,041 --> 01:10:42,275
till you hear
  what I have to say.

1587
01:10:42,342 --> 01:10:44,811
She spoke to me
  last night.

1588
01:10:44,878 --> 01:10:46,279
All right,
I'm calling the police.

1589
01:10:46,346 --> 01:10:47,447
I know it's hard
 to believe.

1590
01:10:47,514 --> 01:10:48,548
I mean it, Charlie.
Get out!

1591
01:10:48,615 --> 01:10:49,716
That's what
  she wants.

1592
01:10:49,783 --> 01:10:51,484
I know that
      would make her happy.

1593
01:10:51,551 --> 01:10:52,819
Happy?

1594
01:10:52,886 --> 01:10:54,421
Happy.

1595
01:10:54,487 --> 01:10:56,856
My mother doesn't even know
she's my mother.

1596
01:10:56,923 --> 01:10:57,991
She doesn't hear me.

1597
01:10:58,058 --> 01:10:58,992
She doesn't see me.

1598
01:10:59,059 --> 01:11:00,393
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

1599
01:11:00,460 --> 01:11:02,495
When you look in her eyes,
you see absolutely nothing.

1600
01:11:02,562 --> 01:11:03,930
She's not there,
do you understand?

1601
01:11:03,997 --> 01:11:06,499
I'm watching
my mother die bit by bit.

1602
01:11:06,566 --> 01:11:08,601
So don't you tell me
about my mother.

1603
01:11:08,668 --> 01:11:09,769
Get out of here!

1604
01:11:09,836 --> 01:11:11,571
Just go!

1605
01:11:13,640 --> 01:11:16,009
I love you, Rose.

1606
01:11:27,320 --> 01:11:29,122
Did you do that
  to yourself, Jules?

1607
01:11:29,189 --> 01:11:31,091
No.

1608
01:11:31,157 --> 01:11:33,259
Well, there are some people
here at the hospital

1609
01:11:33,326 --> 01:11:35,829
that think you might have.

1610
01:11:35,895 --> 01:11:37,931
Hey, look,
this is bull have to
go through with this?

1611
01:11:38,031 --> 01:11:41,334
If you want
    to leave, yes.

1612
01:11:41,401 --> 01:11:42,535
All right.

1613
01:11:42,602 --> 01:11:44,604
Fine.

1614
01:11:44,671 --> 01:11:45,939
I'll play
this game.

1615
01:11:46,006 --> 01:11:48,842
My dad died
when I was real young.

1616
01:11:48,908 --> 01:11:50,176
My mother
      married some guy

1617
01:11:50,243 --> 01:11:52,379
with quick hands
  who didn't have time for me.

1618
01:11:52,445 --> 01:11:53,713
So he hit you?

1619
01:11:53,780 --> 01:11:54,748
Yes.

1620
01:11:54,814 --> 01:11:55,749
A lot?

1621
01:11:55,815 --> 01:11:57,117
When he felt like it.

1622
01:11:57,183 --> 01:11:58,852
They still married?

1623
01:11:58,918 --> 01:12:00,220
I heard he died
years ago,

1624
01:12:00,286 --> 01:12:02,522
which made me
very happy.

1625
01:12:02,589 --> 01:12:04,457
When was the last time
      you spoke to your mother?

1626
01:12:04,524 --> 01:12:06,860
I told you,
I don't have a mother.

1627
01:12:06,926 --> 01:12:08,461
I want to help you, Jules,

1628
01:12:08,528 --> 01:12:09,963
but unless
you tell me the truth,

1629
01:12:10,030 --> 01:12:10,930
I can't.

1630
01:12:10,997 --> 01:12:12,732
So tell me,

1631
01:12:12,799 --> 01:12:15,068
did you do that
  to your hand?

1632
01:12:16,870 --> 01:12:19,305
Yes.

1633
01:12:19,372 --> 01:12:21,441
Why?

1634
01:12:24,144 --> 01:12:25,478
By the time I was 14,

1635
01:12:25,545 --> 01:12:27,714
I was taking a beating
    every day.

1636
01:12:27,781 --> 01:12:29,449
And once,
 it got so bad,

1637
01:12:29,516 --> 01:12:30,550
he even threw
 my mother

1638
01:12:30,617 --> 01:12:32,218
halfway across the room.

1639
01:12:32,285 --> 01:12:34,754
And that's when
    I told him to stop.

1640
01:12:34,821 --> 01:12:36,389
That's all I said.

1641
01:12:36,456 --> 01:12:37,691
"Stop it."

1642
01:12:37,757 --> 01:12:39,526
And you know what he did?

1643
01:12:39,592 --> 01:12:42,295
He broke my nose
in three places

1644
01:12:42,362 --> 01:12:44,297
and then threw me
      out of the house.

1645
01:12:46,099 --> 01:12:47,500
And after
      they fixed me up,

1646
01:12:47,567 --> 01:12:48,802
the hospital
      called my mother,

1647
01:12:48,868 --> 01:12:50,470
and she never showed.

1648
01:12:50,537 --> 01:12:53,039
Never even picked me up.

1649
01:12:53,106 --> 01:12:55,775
Maybe she was scared, Jules.

1650
01:12:55,842 --> 01:12:57,610
Maybe she was just as scared
as you

1651
01:12:57,677 --> 01:13:00,914
when she allowed those things
      to happen to you.

1652
01:13:00,980 --> 01:13:02,816
She might have been happy
     when you ran away

1653
01:13:02,882 --> 01:13:07,420
because she knew
  he couldn't hurt you anymore.

1654
01:13:07,487 --> 01:13:09,689
Maybe she loved you that much.

1655
01:13:09,756 --> 01:13:13,126
Why don't you call her?

1656
01:13:13,193 --> 01:13:15,762
I'm sure she'd love
      to hear from you.

1657
01:13:15,829 --> 01:13:17,430
I can't.

1658
01:13:17,497 --> 01:13:22,168
It's just a phone call, Jules.

1659
01:13:22,268 --> 01:13:23,870
No one should be stuck

1660
01:13:23,937 --> 01:13:25,138
in an emergency room
       on Christmas

1661
01:13:25,205 --> 01:13:28,074
if they don't want to be.

1662
01:13:30,677 --> 01:13:32,879
Be back
in a few minutes.

1663
01:13:41,454 --> 01:13:44,357
[somber music]

1664
01:13:44,424 --> 01:13:52,332
^^ ^^

1665
01:14:12,218 --> 01:14:15,388
I thought I was never
  gonna see you again.

1666
01:14:15,455 --> 01:14:17,657
Hey.

1667
01:14:17,724 --> 01:14:19,225
Long time
  no see.

1668
01:14:21,494 --> 01:14:23,229
Should I get the nurse?

1669
01:14:23,296 --> 01:14:25,165
No.

1670
01:14:27,100 --> 01:14:29,336
What are you still doing here?

1671
01:14:29,402 --> 01:14:32,105
I was waiting for you
    to wake up.

1672
01:14:33,540 --> 01:14:35,275
Thanks so much
    for helping me out.

1673
01:14:35,342 --> 01:14:38,778
I'm very--
very grateful.

1674
01:14:38,845 --> 01:14:42,015
You're welcome.

1675
01:14:50,757 --> 01:14:53,960
Artie,
     listen to me.

1676
01:14:54,027 --> 01:14:56,796
I want you
  to know something.

1677
01:14:59,699 --> 01:15:01,368
I forgive you.

1678
01:15:03,169 --> 01:15:04,671
You understand?

1679
01:15:07,374 --> 01:15:10,143
It's over.

1680
01:15:10,210 --> 01:15:12,012
I forgive you
for everything.

1681
01:15:21,187 --> 01:15:22,722
[gasping]

1682
01:15:29,162 --> 01:15:30,697
Looks like there's somebody
 okto see you.

1683
01:15:40,440 --> 01:15:41,941
Hello, son.

1684
01:15:42,008 --> 01:15:44,377
Hey, Pop.

1685
01:15:46,513 --> 01:15:48,982
You okay?

1686
01:15:49,049 --> 01:15:51,951
[melodramatic music]

1687
01:15:52,018 --> 01:15:59,993
^^ ^^

1688
01:16:33,393 --> 01:16:34,327
Nina, dear.

1689
01:16:34,394 --> 01:16:36,863
I'll be right there.

1690
01:16:36,930 --> 01:16:38,498
Ay, Nina.

1691
01:16:38,565 --> 01:16:40,834
Come and see
 what I see.

1692
01:16:57,751 --> 01:16:59,552
What are you
  doing here?

1693
01:16:59,619 --> 01:17:02,055
Listen, I've been thinking
about what you said last night,

1694
01:17:02,122 --> 01:17:03,923
about being scared.

1695
01:17:03,990 --> 01:17:05,725
I shouldn't have
    said it like that.

1696
01:17:05,792 --> 01:17:08,094
No, I know what you meant.

1697
01:17:08,161 --> 01:17:09,763
But you're wrong.

1698
01:17:09,829 --> 01:17:11,131
I'm the one
 that's scared,

1699
01:17:11,197 --> 01:17:13,600
not you.

1700
01:17:13,667 --> 01:17:16,770
Look, it's not
  that I don't trust you, Nina.

1701
01:17:16,836 --> 01:17:18,171
I don't trust
      who I am,

1702
01:17:18,238 --> 01:17:20,373
you know?

1703
01:17:20,440 --> 01:17:22,175
What you see
 in me.

1704
01:17:22,242 --> 01:17:25,945
You know,
      I'm just a cop, you know?

1705
01:17:26,012 --> 01:17:28,281
I...

1706
01:17:28,348 --> 01:17:29,582
I don't have
  a fancy suit

1707
01:17:29,649 --> 01:17:30,884
or a fancy degree
  on the wall.

1708
01:17:30,950 --> 01:17:32,252
I don't have the words

1709
01:17:32,318 --> 01:17:33,620
to make all the things I did
      go away.

1710
01:17:33,687 --> 01:17:34,921
I wish I did,
  but I don't.

1711
01:17:36,556 --> 01:17:39,893
I just know I want to spend
  the rest of my life with you.

1712
01:17:39,959 --> 01:17:41,795
[sighs]

1713
01:17:41,861 --> 01:17:43,430
Michael...

1714
01:17:44,898 --> 01:17:46,933
Look, if you don't want
to get married,

1715
01:17:47,000 --> 01:17:48,401
it's fine.

1716
01:17:48,468 --> 01:17:50,003
You don't want
    to see me anymore,

1717
01:17:50,070 --> 01:17:51,438
all right.

1718
01:17:51,504 --> 01:17:53,573
You don't even know
      if you love me anymore...

1719
01:17:55,008 --> 01:17:56,543
well, I'll just have to
  accept that,

1720
01:17:56,609 --> 01:17:59,012
because you're more important
to me than us.

1721
01:18:02,082 --> 01:18:03,817
But if you give me
      one more chance--

1722
01:18:03,883 --> 01:18:05,151
I know I've said this before,

1723
01:18:05,218 --> 01:18:08,121
but this time,
    this is for life--

1724
01:18:08,188 --> 01:18:09,956
I won't let you down.

1725
01:18:10,023 --> 01:18:12,826
I won't--
 I won't let you down.

1726
01:18:12,892 --> 01:18:14,260
You have to believe me.
  I've changed.

1727
01:18:14,327 --> 01:18:16,629
I'm not the same anymore.

1728
01:18:16,696 --> 01:18:18,465
[sighing]
  Mike.

1729
01:18:18,531 --> 01:18:19,499
You don't
 have to say

1730
01:18:19,566 --> 01:18:20,900
anything
    right now.

1731
01:18:20,967 --> 01:18:22,268
I want you to think
    about what I just told you.

1732
01:18:22,335 --> 01:18:24,471
You know,
 it's like you used to tell me.

1733
01:18:24,537 --> 01:18:26,439
I mean, this is it.

1734
01:18:26,506 --> 01:18:28,208
This is forever,

1735
01:18:28,274 --> 01:18:29,976
and I want you
    to be sure.

1736
01:18:33,213 --> 01:18:34,881
Okay?

1737
01:18:38,518 --> 01:18:39,753
All right.

1738
01:18:42,055 --> 01:18:44,090
Hey, you know,
one more thing.

1739
01:18:44,157 --> 01:18:47,127
Whatever you decide,
      be happy,

1740
01:18:47,193 --> 01:18:50,697
because that's more important
  to me than anything.

1741
01:18:55,568 --> 01:18:58,471
th
[somber music]

1742
01:18:58,538 --> 01:19:07,047
^^ ^^

1743
01:19:08,014 --> 01:19:09,182
(Rose)
 Excuse me, nurse.

1744
01:19:09,249 --> 01:19:11,251
Have you seen the gentleman
that visits this patient?

1745
01:19:11,317 --> 01:19:12,852
No one comes
      to visit him.

1746
01:19:12,919 --> 01:19:14,320
I've never seen anyone.

1747
01:19:14,387 --> 01:19:15,722
His friend's name
is Charlie Boyd,

1748
01:19:15,789 --> 01:19:17,457
and I saw him here myself
yesterday morning.

1749
01:19:17,524 --> 01:19:18,591
You're mistaken,
    ma'am.

1750
01:19:18,658 --> 01:19:20,026
This is Charles Boyd,

1751
01:19:20,093 --> 01:19:21,561
and no one has ever
come to see him.

1752
01:19:21,628 --> 01:19:22,729
Excuse me.

1753
01:19:22,796 --> 01:19:24,597
I have rounds
to make.

1754
01:19:45,852 --> 01:19:47,721
[whispering]
      Charlie.

1755
01:19:47,787 --> 01:19:50,156
Oh, my God.

1756
01:19:50,223 --> 01:19:52,392
It is you.

1757
01:19:54,928 --> 01:19:57,797
[melodramatic music]

1758
01:19:57,864 --> 01:20:05,772
^^ ^^

1759
01:20:13,346 --> 01:20:14,948
Hey, Charlie.

1760
01:20:17,884 --> 01:20:24,858
^^ ^^

1761
01:20:24,924 --> 01:20:27,761
Charlie.

1762
01:20:27,827 --> 01:20:29,262
Hi.

1763
01:20:37,303 --> 01:20:38,672
It's okay.

1764
01:20:40,573 --> 01:20:42,742
I'm here now, Charlie.

1765
01:20:45,945 --> 01:20:48,615
You can leave now.

1766
01:20:48,682 --> 01:20:50,917
It's okay
to let go.

1767
01:21:01,828 --> 01:21:04,330
Look what
you forgot.

1768
01:21:14,140 --> 01:21:20,113
^^ ^^

1769
01:21:20,180 --> 01:21:21,614
Thank you, Charlie.

1770
01:22:13,166 --> 01:22:14,668
[knocking]

1771
01:22:20,407 --> 01:22:21,641
Hi.

1772
01:22:22,776 --> 01:22:23,777
Hi.

1773
01:22:25,211 --> 01:22:26,613
Can I come in?

1774
01:22:26,680 --> 01:22:29,215
Yeah, come on in.

1775
01:22:34,754 --> 01:22:37,757
I thought I'd come by and...

1776
01:22:37,824 --> 01:22:40,060
give you your gift.

1777
01:22:42,262 --> 01:22:44,998
Where is it?

1778
01:22:50,503 --> 01:22:52,105
It's right here.

1779
01:23:01,181 --> 01:23:03,717
Merry Christmas, Mike.

1780
01:23:03,783 --> 01:23:06,786
Really?

1781
01:23:08,688 --> 01:23:10,724
Really?

1782
01:23:10,790 --> 01:23:13,026
Yeah.

1783
01:23:15,261 --> 01:23:16,930
Oh, I love you.

1784
01:23:16,996 --> 01:23:18,031
I love you.

1785
01:23:18,098 --> 01:23:19,666
So will you
      marry me now?

1786
01:23:19,733 --> 01:23:22,202
Yeah.

1787
01:23:22,268 --> 01:23:23,603
Let's get married.

1788
01:23:23,670 --> 01:23:25,305
Oh, my God.
  I missed you.

1789
01:23:25,372 --> 01:23:27,907
I love you
      so much.

1790
01:23:45,225 --> 01:23:46,960
So, Helen,
do you think your daughter

1791
01:23:47,027 --> 01:23:48,862
would go out
  to dinner with me?

1792
01:23:48,928 --> 01:23:50,597
You know,
  I was hoping

1793
01:23:50,663 --> 01:23:52,799
you might put in
    a good word for me.

1794
01:23:52,866 --> 01:23:54,668
What do you think?

1795
01:23:54,734 --> 01:23:55,669
I'm a nice--

1796
01:23:55,735 --> 01:23:56,903
She's eating.

1797
01:23:56,970 --> 01:23:59,673
Mom, you're eating.

1798
01:23:59,739 --> 01:24:01,307
That's so great.

1799
01:24:01,374 --> 01:24:04,010
Congratulations.

1800
01:24:04,077 --> 01:24:05,011
I was just--

1801
01:24:05,078 --> 01:24:06,880
You're talking,
I know that.

1802
01:24:06,946 --> 01:24:07,881
She's a great listener.

1803
01:24:07,947 --> 01:24:09,616
Yes, she is.

1804
01:24:09,683 --> 01:24:11,818
I suppose I should
continue my rounds.

1805
01:24:11,885 --> 01:24:13,019
Oh, Doctor.

1806
01:24:15,655 --> 01:24:17,557
What's your first name?

1807
01:24:19,626 --> 01:24:20,760
Matthew.

1808
01:24:20,827 --> 01:24:21,861
Matthew.

1809
01:24:21,928 --> 01:24:25,432
That's Matthew, Mom.

1810
01:24:25,498 --> 01:24:26,700
I'm sorry
  about what you heard

1811
01:24:26,766 --> 01:24:28,068
when I was talking
to your mother.

1812
01:24:30,003 --> 01:24:32,272
You know, as a doctor, you say
things to your patients that--

1813
01:24:32,339 --> 01:24:35,342
You don't really mean.

1814
01:24:35,408 --> 01:24:36,776
No, no,
    it's just that sometimes--

1815
01:24:36,843 --> 01:24:39,546
You don't...you don't want
  to take me to dinner.

1816
01:24:39,612 --> 01:24:40,547
No.

1817
01:24:40,613 --> 01:24:43,116
I mean yes.

1818
01:24:43,183 --> 01:24:44,684
I would like
to take you to dinner.

1819
01:24:46,419 --> 01:24:47,921
Oh.

1820
01:24:47,987 --> 01:24:49,889
Well, good,
because, uh...

1821
01:24:49,956 --> 01:24:53,126
Well, I think,
    I think that's a good idea.

1822
01:24:53,193 --> 01:24:54,627
Really?

1823
01:24:54,694 --> 01:24:57,764
Yes.

1824
01:24:57,831 --> 01:24:59,366
That's great.

1825
01:24:59,432 --> 01:25:01,034
I would really like that.

1826
01:25:01,101 --> 01:25:02,836
Me too.

1827
01:25:02,902 --> 01:25:04,671
Merry Christmas, Rose.

1828
01:25:04,738 --> 01:25:08,942
Merry Christmas, Matthew.

1829
01:25:11,177 --> 01:25:12,979
You too, Helen.

1830
01:25:15,015 --> 01:25:17,117
He seems like
  a good guy.

